g delivery for these initiatives. </p><p>  </p><p><strong>Responsibilities</strong> </p><p>• Architect and implement scalable and robust algorithms for price optimization </p><p>• Develop mathematical and statistical models for predicting product performance </p><p>• Conduct data mining and analysis to uncover trends and correlations to better predict business results </p><p>• Analyze customer usage trends to help shape product development strategy </p><p>• Translate mathematical insights into business impact through effective communication of actionable results to both technical and non-technical stakeholders </p><p>• Identify data gaps and new data sources needed to improve model predictive capabilities </p><p><strong> </strong> </p><p><strong>Basic Qualifications</strong> </p><p>• Ph.D. in a quantitative discipline such as Statistics, Math, Engineering, Physical Sciences, Computer Science, Economics or equivalent </p><p>• 3+ years of industry experience in a relevant quantitative field of work </p><p>• 5+ years of experience working with machine learning algorithms, regression, advanced statistical analysis, and mathematical optimization </p><p>• 3+ years of experience working with R, Python, and SQL </p><p>  </p><p><strong>Desired Qualifications</strong> </p><p>• Strong interpersonal skills with a diverse set of constituencies </p><p>• Demonstrated success presenting complex findings in a clear and compelling story that inspires action </p><p>• Not afraid of the question: “Here’s a bunch of data, what can you make of it?” </p><p>• A self-starter with a strong drive to achieve </p><p>• Curiosity and a passion for continuous learning </p><p>• Knowledge of high-tech Internet industry </p><p>• Experience with distributed or parallel computing methodologies such as MapReduce, Hadoop, and Spark </p><p>• Experience with implementing Big Data infrastructure </p><p>  </p><p><strong>Why work here:</strong> </p><p>Simply put this is one of the fastest growing tech companie